// Hand-maintained: NOT generated by mmtorust.
//
// `BackendDAEEXT` is an `external "C"` package whose bodies live in
// `OMCompiler/Compiler/runtime/BackendDAEEXT.cpp` (mark bit-vectors + the
// strongly-connected/low-link state) plus the Kaya/Langguth/Ucar "matchmaker"
// maximum-cardinality bipartite-matching library
// (`OMCompiler/Compiler/runtime/matching.c`, `matching_cheap.c`, the tinymt64
// PRNG). mmtorust can only emit `todo!()` for `external "C"` bodies, so this
// module is hand-written and `BackendDAEEXT` is listed in
// `HANDWRITTEN_TOP_PACKAGES` (mmtorust/src/codegen.rs) to skip its codegen.
//
// The C runtime keeps all of this in process-global `static`s and assumes the
// `setAdjacencyMatrix` → `matching` → `getAssignment` sequence runs serially on
// one logical task. We mirror that in a `thread_local!` `RefCell` (the
// established pattern for the per-task runtime state in this port, see
// `ErrorExt.rs`): it keeps the workspace per-thread without a lock on the hot
// matching path, and the three calls of a matching always run on the same
// thread within one backend function.
//
// The matchmaker algorithms are a faithful translation of the C: pure integer
// array kernels, `int` indices kept as `i32` (so `-1` sentinels and the
// stack/queue underflow checks behave exactly as in C) and cast to `usize` only
// at the indexing site.

